FBIS4-40109 "drsov114_e_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-114 Daily Report 13 Jun 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Kiev Protests Illegal Military Equipment Transfers Kiev Protests Illegal Military Equipment Transfers LD1306151794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English GMT 1330 GMT 13 Jun 94 LD1306151794 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] [Text] Moscow 13 June TASS -- Ukraine's Navy leaders protested on Monday [13 June] the illegal transfer of property from the Black Sea Fleet. In a letter to the Black Sea Fleet commanders, Ukrainian Navy officers said that military equipment and property are being illegally transferred from the Crimean navy base and other units. The letter recalled that the transportation of military equipment in Ukraine must be approved by the Ukrainian chief of general staff. The authors of the letter regretted that such actions are happening at a time when the future of the Black Sea Fleet remains unclear and expressed the hope that the Black Sea Fleet commanders will ensure the enforcement of law and order in their units.
